doc.after: Australia has six states New South Wales NSW Queensland QLD South Australia SA Tasmania TAS Victoria VIC and Western Australia WA and two major mainland territories the Australian Capital Territory ACT and the Northern Territory NT In most respects these two territories function as states but the Commonwealth Parliament can override any legislation of their parliaments By contrast federal legislation overrides state legislation only in areas that are set out in Section 51 of the Australian Constitution state parliaments retain all residual legislative powers including those over schools state police the state judiciary roads public transport and local government since these do not fall under the provisions listed in Section 51 107
